tions as they struggle with rapid changes in the global economy, their country, and their lives. It reverberates far beyond the Argentine oil fields and offers a fresh approach to the critical study of neoliberalism, kinship, citizenship, and corporations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aCitizenshipzArgentina. 0aKinshipxPolitical aspectszArgentina. 0aNeoliberalismzArgentina. 0aPetroleum industry and tradexPolitical aspectszArgentina. 0aPetroleum industry and tradexSocial aspectszArgentina. 0aProtest movementszArgentina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478320040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804783200423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804783200.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles